      public boolean eventClicked​(float mouseX, float mouseY)
      This function is called when the mouse is clicked. If an event is active, check if the user has clicked on the event popup, If yes, remove it and return true. Otherwise, return false
      Parameters:
      mouseX - x coordinate of the mouse when it was pressed
      mouseY - y coordinate of the mouse when it was pressed

    • update

      public void update​(java.util.Observable obs, java.lang.Object obj)
      This function is called every minute. Every minute there's a chance (denoted by the chanceOfEvent vaiable) that an event fires, the player has a set amout of seconds after an event fires to react, otherwise that family member gets sick, or dies. To react to these events, the player will have to left click on the pop-up once it fires
      Specified by:
      update in interface java.util.Observer
